"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-06-20-use-african-championship-as-olympic-rehearsal-sports-minister-enoh-to-nigerian-athletes\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  on  By  The Honourable Minister of Sports Development, Senator John Owan Enoh, has urged Nigerian athletes to treat the upcoming African Championship in Cameroon as a perfect rehearsal for the Olympic Games in Paris later this year.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 100, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999996397448934, \"rank\": 3.3734472380094134e-07, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}, {\"begin\": 164, \"end\": 172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameroon_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9991129903764122, \"rank\": 0.0008877968544500311, \"text\": \"Cameroon\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameroon_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameroon_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 221, \"end\": 226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999996874733403, \"rank\": 3.1252682583495895e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was disclosed in a statement by Diana-Mary Nsan, Senior Assistance on Media to the Minister of Sports Development, on Thursday.\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Enoh stated this following the Athletics Federation of Nigeria's AFN, announcement of a formidable list of 40 athletes that will represent the country at the African Championships in Douala.\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 444, \"end\": 447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Assembly_of_First_Nations\", \"score\": 0.947833012368471, \"rank\": 0.055037667068117996, \"text\": \"AFN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Assembly_of_First_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Assembly_of_First_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 562, \"end\": 568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Douala\", \"score\": 0.9999999594638219, \"rank\": 3.7628082067299233e-08, \"text\": \"Douala\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Douala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Douala\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the standout names are Tobi Amusan, Favour Ofili, Chukwuebuka Enekwechi, and Chidi Okezie, some of Nigeria's biggest stars heading to the competition.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oluwatobiloba_Amusan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tobi Amusan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oluwatobiloba_Amusan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oluwatobiloba_Amusan\"}, {\"begin\": 627, \"end\": 648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chukwuebuka_Enekwechi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chukwuebuka Enekwechi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chukwuebuka_Enekwechi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chukwuebuka_Enekwechi\"}, {\"begin\": 654, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chidi_Okezie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chidi Okezie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chidi_Okezie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chidi_Okezie\"}, {\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999804028905, \"rank\": 1.9597202281676464e-08, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Minister emphasized the importance of this championship as a precursor to the Olympics, highlighting its role in preparing athletes for podium success at the world's biggest sporting event in Paris.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 925, \"end\": 930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999996874733403, \"rank\": 3.1252682583495895e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The African Athletics Championship should serve as a dress rehearsal for the Olympics,\\\" Enoh stated.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I charge all our flag bearers to represent the green and white flag with pride and aim to bring back the first position trophy at the end of the tournament.\\\"\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also advised the athletes to be cautious about their diet and hydration, noting the significance of this Olympic year and the heightened scrutiny they will face.\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CAF to make 2024 WAFCON, 2025 AFCON announcements Friday  Transfer: We have to wait - Agent on Osimhen's next destination  PDP Rep, Etteh backs Gov Eno's endorsement of Tinubu for 2027  Alleged 'demotion' of Enoh to junior minister angers Cross River radio callers  Libya: You have gone through near-death experience - Sports Minister, Enoh tells Super Eagles  AFCON 2025 qualifier: Sports Minister Enoh praises Super Eagles duo after win over Libya  AFCON 2025 qualifier: Do not undermine Libya - Sports Minister, Enoh warns Super Eagles  Super Eagles: Labbadia walking out on NFF very embarrassing - Sports Minister, Enoh  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media 